Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Sostratos. Trimmed. Probably from the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 104.18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0846)
